{
  "answer": "**The specific verses listing the eight kinds (or forms) of marriage in the *Viṣṇu Smṛti* are found in Chapter 24, verses 17–18.**\n\nThere, it states:\n\n> Now, there are eight forms of marriage.[^1]  \n> The Brāhma, Daiva, Ārṣa, Prājāpatya, Gāndharva, Āsura, Rākṣasa, and Paiśāca.[^2]\n\nThe text then describes each form in the following verses (19–26) and notes that the first four are righteous (verse 27).[^3]\n\n[^1]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 24, paragraph p-5a5a7f](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/24/translation/#p-5a5a7f).\n\n[^2]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 24, paragraph p-3a34b6](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/24/translation/#p-3a34b6).\n\n[^3]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 24](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/24/translation/).",
